{
  "texts": [
    "Probabilistic PCA and Bayesian variants sample posteriors for latent factors and missing values, enabling uncertainty-aware imputations [6].",
    "When correlations are captured by a few components, these methods achieve high accuracy with modest computation.",
    "Beyond low rank, distribution alignment casts imputation as matching empirical distributions of observed and completed data.",
    "Optimal Transport provides a geometric formulation solved via entropy-regularized Sinkhorn iterations [14]; recent OT-based imputers align distributions while controlling reconstruction cost and preserving structure [31].Deep generative models learn flexible conditional distributions for missing values.",
    "VAE-based methods reconstruct masked inputs through encoder-decoder architectures; MIWAE improves training via importance weighting, and VAEAC supports arbitrary missingness patterns [17], [16]."
  ]
}